Put a Pic on It!

Called like:

http://putapicon.it/:width/:height?q=:image_search_string
e.g. http://putapicon.it/400/200?q=puppies

or 

http://putapicon.it/:square?q=image_search_string
e.g. http://putapicon.it/350?q=kittens

or

http://putapicon.it/:width_by_height?q=image_search_string
e.g. http://putapicon.it/350x450?q=cute+animals

or 

http://putapicon.it/:common_ad_size?q=image_search_string
e.g. http://putapicon.it/skyscraper?q=bicycles


The first time a query string is used, we have to run a Google image search, download the original images,
and resize them to your specification. After that, the image is cached and ready to go in that size. If you 
request another size with the same query string we skip the download and just resize the cached originals.